race.comment: WIMOWEH (10) finished third, beaten 2 lengths, when resuming from a spell last start over 1400m at Beaudesert after she was prominent at the bend. Strips fitter and has the class to take care of this field. FORTUNAS GIRL (6) was out of the money on debut two runs back then just missed the frame last start over 1100m at Gold Coast, beaten 6 lengths into fifth. Finds a nice race and can take this out. BLOOD RED (1) resumes from a spell of five months. Could only manage to finish tenth at the latest run over 1600m at Sunshine Coast. Has ability and is a leading player. GRIGIA (7) showed early speed from an outside draw last time and led for much of the way before fading to finish sixth, beaten 4 lengths, over 1350m at Ipswich. Worth including in calculations.
